# Environment variables and secrets
.env
*.env
.env.local

# Python cache
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd

# Virtual environments
venv/
env/
.venv/

# Test cache
.pytest_cache/
*.egg-info/

# OS files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# VibeBench output files (optional — remove if you want to commit results)
vibebench_multimodel_*.json
```

Commit directly to main with message:
```
Add .gitignore to prevent committing secrets and cache files
```

---

Then immediately after, create another new file called `.env.example`:
```
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your keys
# NEVER commit .env to GitHub

GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key_here
GROQ_API_KEY=your_groq_api_key_here
OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_api_key_here
